<h2>INF 102 Concept of Programming Languages II</h2>

<table border="1" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0"
style="border-collapse: collapse" width="100%" id="AutoNumber1">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td width="80%" valign="top"><font size="4"
        face="Pristina"><b>Synopsis</b></font> 

        <p><b>Purpose.</b>  In-depth study of major programming
paradigms: imperative, functional, declarative, object-oriented, 
aspect-oriented, and much more! Understanding the role of programming languages in
software development and the suitability of languages in
context. 

       <p><b>Textbook: </b> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Exercises-Programming-Style-Cristina-Videira/dp/1482227371/">Exercises in Programming Style</a><br/>
          <b>Code:</b> <a href="https://github.com/crista/exercises-in-programming-style">Github</a></p>

       <p><b>Evaluation.</b>
        Up to 9 projects. Each project is worth up to 100 points. 
